The paper focuses on the application of GANs in information retrieval scenarios, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of GANs and their application in fitting discrete data, which are topics that are closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
